by ktomk at 2019-10-02T09:22:53Z

This is not PHP 7.4,  it's the snapshot. Would be same as with master. They normally fail in the build (speaking of my own projects), so I allow snapshots / nightlies / masters to fail. I only need to check them when I want to learn how it is going on and for upstream reporting (e.g. PHP bugs etc.).

Not allowing failure for unstable run-times in the build must ask for something very specific to  argue for the burden this creates (e.g. my PRs fail here b/c of that, see #4550). I would love to learn about the specifics that weight the burden.

Here per reference how I got the PHP-CS-Fixer build green again:

* https://github.com/FriendsOfPHP/PHP-CS-Fixer/commit/4354a5ecb2f3b63207784b72830b7f445e463a02
* Green Build Example: https://travis-ci.org/FriendsOfPHP/PHP-CS-Fixer/builds/592276115 (green builds are currently easy to find on Travis though)

