by kubawerlos at 2019-10-02T20:57:06Z

@julienfalque I like to rely on CI checks and here we have clear situation that unstable PHP version fails CI due to its bug, We are far from supporting PHP 7.4, so why do we require it to pass tests? It's not like we would have dozens of failing tests when we allow it to fail.

I bet there would be people (including myself) checking the reason of PHP 7.4 failure even if failure would be allowed.

Especially I'm not updating my PRs recently as the would fail CI anyway (like [this](https://github.com/FriendsOfPHP/PHP-CS-Fixer/pull/4556) one, which passes all but PHP 7.4) - it simply feels like I know I will get ~finger~ "rejected" by CI, so why to bother?

